Nigerian Afro fusion artist, Louis Favour aka Dredi has released her debut song  entitled You be Man. After a listening party scheduled for today, Wednesday July 20, 2022, ‘ You be Man’ is scheduled for a release on Thursday July 21, 2022.   Seven Nigerian celebrities with honorary doctorate degrees     Davido congratulates Adeleke for receiving certificate of…     Apostle Chibuzor withdraws Aguba’s marriage gifts, transfers…   Speaking on the motive behind the song, Dredi disclosed that ‘You be Man’ explains the strength of a scorned woman, woman who has been through so much for love and ended up broken from it and her only escape is making every other man reap the fruit the other men have planted, she’s still open to love but only if he’s willing to face her wrath forever. Inspired by the works of Nicki Minaj, Rihanna, Jesse J, Sean Paul, Adele amongst others, Dredi established an early interest in music while growing up which led to joining her church choir and being exposed to the basics of music. Currently residing in Lagos, the 21 year old musician infuses smooth Afro beats and R&B into contemporary reggae.